My opinion's<br>
<br>
I think the Summoned Focus items Rock<br>
I think Magician Summoned Items should be the best in the game <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> as far as the effect is concearned</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->. If there is a peice of AoW loot that has better AC, more HP on it etc... , that is fine, but imo it shouldnt exceed the 20% damage bonus that the bracer can give you<br>
I agree with the change to the Ring for healing spells<br>
I agree with the change to the Bracer for Banes<br>
<br>
Some one mentioned a good Idea, caster class specific focus items. I'd love it. One that effected Dots for necro\shammy\druid types, one that did effect clerial healing spells, sure. Good idea, dont think we'll see it.<br>
<br>
In my opinion, you have to give a little, to get a little. When I first casted the spell, I was rather upset that I had to take off some of my current gear, for crappier gear just to get the effect. After some time, it makes sense. Quid Pro Quo.<br>
<br>
As far as people leaving a body with items on it.. is that really necessary? Be nice to your local mage, heaven forbid, invite them into your exp group when they are LFG.<br>
<br>
Flame on,<br>
